Software Engineer

iStreamPlanet

- Seattle, WA 98101 (Denny Triangle area)

While we have offices in Seattle and Las Vegas, we are seeking the best talent to join our team and will consider Remote/Telework options for candidates located anywhere in the US.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Do you enjoy a healthy team environment that supports continuous learning and iterative development? We love cognitive diversity because it helps us deliver ideal outcomes for customers. One of the primary reasons we harmonize and trust one another is because we're aligned on a positive, growth-mindset.

If you love working with a team that is passionate about what they do and how they do it; if you seek a fun work life that fosters an environment of professional and personal growth while celebrating people of all backgrounds, orientations, and identities; we want to meet you.

The Job
-------

We are a group of distributed systems engineers committed to learning, growing, and getting better every day. As a Software Engineer at iStreamPlanet, you will build and operate a platform that delivers the core of our business: media delivery. We use data to solve problems, work with customers to deliver and evolve media standards, believe in operational ownership, and drive continuous improvement. This is a great opportunity for someone who is comfortable working with products with a number of moving pieces and who enjoys learning new technologies.

The Day-to-Day
--------------

Develop and maintain end-to-end platform features.
Assist in the development of loosely-coupled, RESTful services with a bias for simple, elegant solutions.
Improve services reliability and availability by evaluating root causes and implementing fixes.
Debug production issues across services and stacks.
Work within Linux and Open Source Software.
Utilize container systems (Docker) and container orchestration (e.g. ECS/EKS, Kubernetes).
Participate in a 24x7 on-call rotation.
Contribute to a culture of personal and team accountability where the customer, compassion, and team development are the focus.
The Essentials
--------------

Bachelor's degree or equivalent years of experience.
3+ years of relevant distributed systems experience.
Back-end knowledge and willingness to work beyond your comfort zone.
We primarily code in Golang, but no experience is necessary. If you're strong in one or more industry-standard languages (e.g. C/C++/C#/Java/TypeScript/Python), we will coach.
Experience deploying in distributed cloud environments.
Focus on personal and team growth that fosters camaraderie.
Embraces a growth-mindset by continually learning and appropriately applying new techniques, approaches, or technology.
The Perks
---------

Flexible work hours and work from home options
Accessible and transparent leadership team
Paid time off every year to volunteer and generous parental leave
Medical, dental, vision benefits, 401(k) plan with a company match
Part of the WarnerMedia family of powerhouse brands
Who We Are
----------

iStreamPlanet is one of the largest streaming platforms in the world for broadcasters; doing thousands of events a year such as March Madness, World Cup, and even the Olympics. You probably have not heard of us but we power some of the most well-known media brands in the world. Our mission is to provide a one-stop platform for the media industry as they convert from traditional broadcast to all online streaming over the next decade. We are backed by giants such as WarnerMedia (owners of Warner Brothers, HBO, Turner, etc.) and are at the heart of changing how you get your sports and entertainment in the future.

iStreamPlanet Co., LLC is an equal employment opportunity employer. iStreamPlanet does not discriminate against any applicant or employee based on race, color, religion, national origin, gender, age, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, marital status, mental or physical disability, and genetic information, or any other basis protected by applicable law.

